-- Germany’s Free Democrats Abandon Tax-Cut Policy, Die Welt Says
-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 2012-01-31T07:10:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-31/germany-s-free-democrats-abandon-tax-cut-policy-die-welt-says.html
The Free Democratic Party, the
coalition partner of German Chancellor  Angela Merkel ’s Christian
Democrats, has abandoned a call for tax cuts,  Die Welt reported ,
citing a policy statement.  The statement refers to avoiding tax increases, the
newspaper said, adding that emphasis is placed on growth and
spending discipline.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sheenagh Matthews in Frankfurt at 
 smatthews6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
